data.text:
The PlayStation Network, commonly abbreviated to PSN, is the online feature for later PlayStation consoles, starting from PlayStation 3 in 2006. It allows one to use a game's online features, download full games, game demos, game trailers, themes, original soundtracks, and PlayStation titles on the PlayStation Store or interact with other players on PlayStation Home. Downloading games to play and its contents that requires network payment will cost a fee.
